frameDefinitions: This  frame contains words that talk about how Speakers name Entities.
This frame describes food and meal preparation.
An Agent manipulates a Sound_maker or a Cause causes the Sound_maker to emit a sound.
A Selector, often an individual in a leadership role, appoints a Official to assume an official Role in an organization (which can be expressed as the Body).
This frame describes an Agent's gathering of Individuals (people or entities) into a group, the  Aggregate, defined by relative proximity.
frameExamples: They drove through an area <t>nicknamed</t> Sniper's Alley
Caitlin <t>baked</t> some cookies from the pre-packaged dough.
The monks would <t>ring</t> the bell until sundown.
Press secretaries <t>accredit</t> journalists to the sessions.
The police <t>gathered</t> the suspects into a line-up.
listRoleDefinitions: The entity that Speakers refer to by using the Name.
The linguistic expression by which Speakers refer to the Entity.
The person who uses the linguistic expression (Name) to refer to the Referent.
When the event occurs.
Where the event takes place.
The <fen>Cook</fen>  prepares the <fen>Produced_food</fen>.
The <fen>Produced_food</fen> is the result of a <fen>Cook</fen>'s efforts.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the cooking creation occurs.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the cooking creation occurs.
The individual that manipulates a Sound_maker so that it makes Noise.
The entity that produces the Noise, as a result of the action of the Agent.
The inanimate force of nature that causes the <fen>Sound_maker</fen> to produce noise.
The time at which the noise is produced.
The location at which the sound is produced.
The <fen>Selector</fen> is responsible for the appointment of the new official.  Typically, it occurs as the External Argument of verbs.
The <fen>Official</fen> is a person appointed to a recognized position.

Frequently, the <fen>Official</fen> is referred to only by his/her role. However, the <fen>Role</fen> can be expressed separately from the leader, usually as either a secondary predicate or in a PP Complement (headed by <m>as</m>).
The <fen>Function</fen> is the purpose the <fen>Official</fen> will fufill.
A group of individuals who are elected or appointed to perform some function, and to which the <fen>Official</fen> is assigned.
When the designation of the official takes place.
Where the appointment takes place.
This role identifies the aggregate that results from the gathering.  It may be expressed either as an adjunct result phrase or as a direct object of a target verb.
Agent is the person who gathers Individuals.
This role identifies the entities that come together to form an Aggregate.

This role identifies the time when the gathering event occurs, if specified.
The crowd assembled <fex name='Time'>at dawn</fex>.

This role identifies the place where the gathering event occurs.
He <t>assembled</t> the children <fex name='Place'>in the hall</fex>.
listRoleExamples: Drew baked an apple pie <fex>at six int he morning</fex>.
Drew prepared the soup <fex> in the kitchen</fex>.
<fex>You</fex> can ring the bell as often as you'd like.
Under the new program, SCC will accredit organizations <fex>to assess wood flow from certified forests to workshops or factories</fex>.
The police gathered the suspects <fex>into a line-up</fex>.
<fex>The police</fex> gathered the suspects into a lineup.
The police gathered <fex>the suspects</fex> into a line-up.
